  "schema_version": "1.6.2",
  "id": "BIT-parse-2026-34595",
  "summary": "Parse Server: LiveQuery protected-field guard bypass via array-like logical operator value",
  "details": "Parse Server is an open source backend that can be deployed to any infrastructure that can run Node.js. Prior to versions 8.6.70 and 9.7.0, an authenticated user with find class-level permission can bypass the protectedFields class-level permission setting on LiveQuery subscriptions. By sending a subscription with a $or, $and, or $nor operator value as a plain object with numeric keys and a length property (an \"array-like\" object) instead of an array, the protected-field guard is bypassed. The subscription event firing acts as a binary oracle, allowing the attacker to infer whether a protected field matches a given test value. This issue has been patched in versions 8.6.70 and 9.7.0.",
  "aliases": [
    "CVE-2026-34595"
